{"title":"Combined feed","url":"https://Vinnl.github.io/feeds/all.xml","elements":[{"title":"El Sol Rojo (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that <i><b><a href=\"/wiki/El_Sol_Rojo\" title=\"El Sol Rojo\">El Sol Rojo</a></b></i> <i>(pictured)</i>, located adjacent to <a href=\"/wiki/Estadio_Azteca\" title=\"Estadio Azteca\">Mexico City Stadium</a>, has no recognized legal owner?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/El_Sol_Rojo","retrieved":1781463082318},{"title":"Melissa Sevigny (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that science writer <b><a href=\"/wiki/Melissa_Sevigny\" title=\"Melissa Sevigny\">Melissa Sevigny</a></b> took a rafting trip down the Colorado River to research a book?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Melissa_Sevigny","retrieved":1781463082319},{"title":"Daylit Gallery (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that the <b><a href=\"/wiki/Daylit_Gallery\" title=\"Daylit Gallery\">Daylit Gallery</a></b> was once an outdoor utility area?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Daylit_Gallery","retrieved":1781463082319},{"title":"Mordecai Bauman (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that classical singer <b><a href=\"/wiki/Mordecai_Bauman\" title=\"Mordecai Bauman\">Mordecai Bauman</a></b> used his music to support far-left American politics during the 1930s?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mordecai_Bauman","retrieved":1781463082319},{"title":"Snoopy Presents: A Summer Musical (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that one song in <i><b><a href=\"/wiki/Snoopy_Presents:_A_Summer_Musical\" title=\"Snoopy Presents: A Summer Musical\">Snoopy Presents: A Summer Musical</a></b></i> uses a 1950s <i><a href=\"/wiki/Peanuts\" title=\"Peanuts\">Peanuts</a></i> art style that the comic strip's original creator disliked?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Snoopy_Presents:_A_Summer_Musical","retrieved":1781463082320},{"title":"Abdurrahman Gunadirdja (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that diplomat <b><a href